    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26b.19-20_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">19</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        Montgomery, West Virginia
                        July 23, 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>My dear Friend:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Doctor Laird tells me that Mrs. Neihardt has "awakened from the dream of life." I know how certain you are that the awakening is the supreme thrill of living and in this certainty there is solace.</p>
                
                <p>But until the time of one's own awakening there is " a loss in all familiar things, in flower that blooms and bird that sings." So I am thinking of you with deep concern.</p>
                
                <p>Your kindness of many summers ago in Chicago I think of often. All of you were most gracious. It was a privilege to meet such a wonderful person as Mrs. Neihardt, a charming hostess, accomplished artist, skilled home-worker, alert to all the varied pulsations of life. In the old-fashioned language of New England, I hope you will be "supported."</p>
                
                <lg>
                    <l>"That such have lived enables us</l>
                    <l>The tranquiler to die;</l>
                    <l>That such have died, certificate</l>
                    <l>Of immortality.</l>
                </lg>
                
                <p>Dr. Laird is being well cared for by his Danish nurse. Mrs. Laird seems a bit better. The college has about ceased to have speakers. Last Fall they recalled one but Dr. Laird did not want me to leave, so I am still at the Hospital.</p>
                
                <p>My Edward and his family are near San Francisco they have two children. I am rather busy. The Karma at the present stage does not make complete sense, but there are days ahead for it to reveal meaning</p>
                
                <p>Many friends are leaving for the further shore, and " we are treading onward too as fast as Time can move."</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Pax vobiscum</salute>
                    
                    <signed>RHV.</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p>Share my greetings!</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
            
